-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Panoro, Rio Cristal, Southern Copper
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-02-14T18:44:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/peru-stocks-buenaventura-panoro-rio-cristal-southern-copper.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:26 p.m.  Lima  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a seventh session, losing
0.5 percent to 22,321.59. The  MSCI (MXPECAPD)  All Peru Capped Index slid 1
percent to 2,802.39.  Mining shares dropped after U.S. stocks and metals
declined, said Estefany Castillo, an analyst at Scotiabank Peru.  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian
exploration company, fell 7.1 percent to 13 cents.  Southern
Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peru’s biggest producer of the metal,
dropped 3.6 percent to $32.10.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a
Canadian exploration company, declined 2.8 percent to $1.05.
 Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the country’s biggest
precious-metals miner, slid 3.3 percent to $39.77.  Panoro
Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold exploration
company, fell 3.2 percent to 60 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
